<div  lang="en">
<ul class="wprm-recipe-instructions" nodeIndex="93"><li class="wprm-recipe-instruction" nodeIndex="92">
<div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" nodeIndex="94">Heat the <a href="http://amzn.to/2rwxqs4" target="_blank" rel="nofollow" nodeIndex="300">Instant Pot</a> to "Saute" and add ghee.</div>
</li>
<li class="wprm-recipe-instruction" nodeIndex="95">
<div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" nodeIndex="96">Once the Instant Pot signals that it's "hot," add in garlic, ginger, serrano or jalape&ntilde;o pepper, and onion.</div>
</li>
<li class="wprm-recipe-instruction" nodeIndex="97">
<div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" nodeIndex="98">Stir cooking for 5 minutes until fragrant.</div>
</li>
<li class="wprm-recipe-instruction" nodeIndex="99">
<div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" nodeIndex="100">Add in the garam masala, cumin, turmeric, sea salt, cayenne (if using), and coconut cream, and stir together.</div>
</li>
<li class="wprm-recipe-instruction" nodeIndex="101">
<div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" nodeIndex="102">Hit "cancel" to turn off the Instant Pot.</div>
</li>
<li class="wprm-recipe-instruction" nodeIndex="103">
<div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" nodeIndex="104">Add in frozen spinach and stir.</div>
</li>
<li class="wprm-recipe-instruction" nodeIndex="105">
<div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" nodeIndex="106">Close the lid, make sure the pressure valve is set to "Sealing," then set it to Manual on high pressure for 15 minutes.</div>
</li>
<li class="wprm-recipe-instruction" nodeIndex="107">
<div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" nodeIndex="108">Quick pressure release once it beeps to a finish.</div>
</li>
<li class="wprm-recipe-instruction" nodeIndex="109">
<div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" nodeIndex="110">Use an immersion blender to blend everything together, or transfer to a regular blender to puree together. I like to leave mine a bit lumpy.</div>
</li>
<li class="wprm-recipe-instruction" nodeIndex="111">
<div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" nodeIndex="112">Stir in apple cider vinegar. Taste and add more salt, if needed.</div>
</li>
<li class="wprm-recipe-instruction" nodeIndex="113">
<div class="wprm-recipe-instruction-text" nodeIndex="114">Serve over cooked chicken and/or cauliflower rice.</div>
</li>
</ul></div>